outputs.output_descr:
This project falls under the program of land development jointly implemented by UNDP and the Ministry of Agriculture (MoA) with the support of local NGOs, aiming at land protection, reducing poverty and improving the living conditions of residents of the area through increasing the arable land area and providing employment opportunities to residents in the rural and marginal areas of Jerusalem District
The project had the following components:
- Strengthening of the local communities and the promotion of their active participation in the planning and implementation of the project's activities;
- Provision of extension and other related agricultural services to the local communities participating in the project;
- Reclamation and development of agricultural land to expand the arable areas and thus increase the local food supply;
- Employment generation through the adoption of labor intensive technologies to develop agricultural lands, water harvesting techniques and any other construction work.
